save *<filename> *<var> *-d *-f
	writes <var> to a csv file.

	*-d deletes variables after they have been written.
	*-f forces appending to the file if it already exists.

You can give more than one <var> argument, separated by whitespaces.
If no variable is specified, all variables will be written.

If no filename is specified, current date and time will be used.